Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveHauwa Mohammed, aka Jaruma, has been ordered back into prison by Justice Ismaila Abdullahi of an Upper Area Court in Abuja.
The judge ordered the police to re-arrest the aphrodisiacs dealer earlier granted bail weeks ago for failing to appear in court Wednesday.
Justice Abdullahi revoked the bail, and He directed that she should be remanded in the Suleja Correctional Centre.
Jaruma got into problem for posting on her Instagram page text billionaire Ned Nwoko considered defamatory about him.
The case has been adjourned to March 17, 2022.
